{"title":"Storck GRIX.2 gravel bike gets full system integration, Classified wireless shifting hub option","link":"https://bikerumor.com/storck-grix-2-gravel-bike-gets-full-system-integration-classified-wireless-shifting-hub-option/","date":1638395727000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike details\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162115/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-5.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-279752\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Building on the racy nature of the original GRIX, the new Storck GRIX.2 gravel bike keeps the short headtube and steeper head angle as the original, but adds all the attachment points you’d want on a performance bike. And, being a Storck, it’s rather light.</p><p>The biggest visual change is the edgier lines and shapes, complemented by full internal routing of all the cables, hoses, and wires. That comes courtesy of the new aero one-piece handlebar-stem unit first seen on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/storck-aerfast4-aero-road-bike-pushes-uci-limits-plus-new-fascenario4-more/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Aerfast3 road bike</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike details\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162113/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>All brake lines and shift wires or cables, if there are any, run all the way through the handlebar, into the integrated stem, and straight into the headtube and frame.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike shown from drive side\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162105/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Storck says the GRIX.2 frame weight starts at just 900g thanks to “using the highest quality fibers.” Storck has always had a penchant for light weight, and this bike’s no different.</p><p>The GRIX.2 keeps the dropped driveside chainstay to eliminate chain slap on rough terrain, and likely add clearance for larger chainrings and 2x cranksets. The bike has a bolt-on front derailleur mount that’s absent on 1x builds.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike details\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3-297x297.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3-800x800.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3-120x120.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162110/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-3-125x125.jpg 125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>New on this model are all the mounts. With three bolts on each fork leg, top tube mounts, and a multi-position arrangement of bolts above and below the downtube, the bike’s able to carry plenty of water and gear.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike closeup on drivetrain\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162124/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>More mounts sit atop the seatstays and at the rear dropout. Bikes will come in this Vulcanic Sunset color with multiple traditional drivetrain builds available. But, the bike shown here is the…</p><h3>Storck x Classified Wireless Hub Build</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike shown with closeup on Classified wireless shifting rear hub\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162121/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The GRIX.2 x Classified build runs €4,199 and gets a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-xplr-gravel-group-debuts-rockshox-fork-dropper-wide-gearing-moto-wheels/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SRAM Force XPLR</a> 1×12 group, adding <a href=\"http://www.classified-cycling.cc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Classified’s Powershift</a> rear hub. By putting a 2-speed system inside the rear hub and giving you wireless control, the bike has all the benefits of a 2x group (potentially with even more range since cassette size is no longer a limiting factor), but with less maintenance and better aerodynamics. Check our <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/classified-adds-wheelsets-with-internal-gearing-so-you-can-double-the-range-of-your-current-1x-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">full tech coverage on Classified here</a> for all the details.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1.jpg\" alt=\"storck grix2 gravel bike shown with closeup on Classified wireless shifting rear hub\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1136\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1-297x211.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1-800x568.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1-120x85.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1-768x545.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/01162118/2022-storck-grix2-gravel-race-bike-classified-wireless-hub-shifting-1-1536x1091.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The only limitations or caveats with the Classified Powershift system is that you’re locking into their wheels for now, and you need a specially modified cassette to fit it (they offer Shimano and SRAM options for now), but they do have three different rims available. That, and when paired with SRAM AXS groups, you’ll get a separate shift button to put on your handlebar somewhere as it won’t receive signals directly from SRAM’s wireless shifters.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.storck-bicycle.de/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Storck-Bicycle.de</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7082ec693fa134dd11d0051ad391700a914f865ac2da7b10c41ec38ef7c30938","category":"Cycling"}